comments:
There were different components (sort of like syllables) that repeated themselves in different objects. Such as "-cf" & -"r\", just as an example.

After the first two or three trials I understood I had to ignore the # at the start and end of the words, after that I focused on giving a sound to sections of word (as I had no time to vocalize the entirety of the word due to time constraint), the more and more I failed the more i managed to vocalize in my head some of those words fully ("toy-cf"."moonlanding","questionmarkalpha").

The second section of the experiment was too quick for my eyes to even catch a glimpse of the entire symbols, so i had to focus on a section of the "word" and hope that it would be enough to recognize it amongst the list.
Even a few more milliseconds I think would have been enough to have a better chance.
